1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,240
 Waiting for something to happen that you're expecting to happen, but that doesn't happen,

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,740
 is really awkward, isn't it?

3
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:14,160
 I just looked around the room whilst you were waiting for me to start.

4
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:17,160
 Normally, I rush into it, don't I?

5
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:21,440
 But as I looked around the room, all of you would not look at me in the eyes at all.

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,520
 It was like a super awkward moment for all of us.

7
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:28,880
 When we're waiting for something to happen and it doesn't happen, we human beings find

8
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:33,480
 it really awkward, really uncomfortable, really strange.

9
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:37,640
 My daughter and I experienced this at the extreme this past week.

10
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:43,120
 We were in Queenstown in New Zealand, and my daughter, as we were about a month ago,

11
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:49,360
 she had said, "Oh, Dad, when we're in Queenstown, I want to do the Canyon Swing," which audibly

12
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,600
 didn't sound that bad, the Canyon Swing.

13
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:53,400
 That sounds like a pretty okay thing.

14
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:57,940
 She sent me some videos of the Canyon Swing, and I saw these videos, and I realized there

15
00:00:57,940 --> 00:01:01,360
 was a 100-meter drop, free fall.

16
00:01:01,360 --> 00:01:03,320
 You're basically sitting in this kind of swing.

17
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:08,040
 You drop for 100 meters, and then you swing out over this massive canyon.

18
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:11,880
 It looked like the worst thing a human being would want to do.

19
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,720
 But my daughter was so excited to do the Canyon Swing.

20
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:16,960
 She's like, "Daddy, you're going to have to do it with me.

21
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:18,400
 You can do it tandem.

22
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:21,720
 We'll sit side by side, and we'll do this crazy thing."

23
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:28,160
 And I thought to myself, "Do I be a good father, or do I be a sane human being?"

24
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:31,320
 So we signed up for the Canyon Swing.

25
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:34,460
 We went up to this high peak above this canyon.

26
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:36,940
 We looked down on this little platform.

27
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:40,540
 There were about 10 of us that were going to do this Canyon Swing, and I said to Mia,

28
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:41,900
 "We're going to have to go first."

29
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:42,900
 She's like, "No, Dad.

30
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:43,900
 No, no, no.

31
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:44,900
 No, I don't want to go first.

32
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:45,900
 Let other people go first."

33
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:50,140
 So I said, "No, no, because if I wait, I will not do it.

34
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,880
 I need to just get up there, and I need to do this.

35
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,040
 I need to get it done.

36
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:56,120
 We need to just get on with it."

37
00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:02,060
 Now the crazy thing about the Canyon Swing is you can decide how you swing off the bridge,

38
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:05,640
 and Mia decided that she wanted to do the chainsaw.

39
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:09,980
 Now the chainsaw requires you to sit down in these harnesses.

40
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:15,940
 They send you out on this crane over the canyon, and they hang you there.

41
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:17,960
 So you've got a hundred meter drop below you.

42
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:22,240
 They hang you there, and then they get out a chainsaw.

43
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:28,400
 And the rope that is holding you in the air, a hundred meters above the canyon, they saw

44
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:31,660
 that rope, and then you go.

45
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:37,620
 So we're hanging out over this canyon, and the lady is standing over us with the chainsaw,

46
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:41,120
 and she's fake-sawing the string, the rope.

47
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:44,700
 So we're hanging there for far longer than we wanted to.

48
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:48,420
 Have you ever been in a situation where you're waiting for something to happen that you think

49
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:51,720
 is going to happen, and it doesn't happen?

50
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:54,820
 That's about the worst thing you could do with the Canyon Swing, okay?

51
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:58,020
 Because you're hanging out over this drop, and suddenly she's like, "Oh, maybe now."

52
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,980
 She's like, "Maybe now.

53
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:00,980
 Maybe now."

54
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:04,220
 And I'm just like, "Cut the swing.

55
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:05,880
 Like I want to go."

56
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:10,540
 And finally she does it, and we plummet, and it was crazy, and my heart rate is pounding

57
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:14,900
 just with the memory of it.

58
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:18,480
 As human beings, we don't like to wait, do we?

59
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:20,020
 Waiting is difficult.

60
00:03:20,020 --> 00:03:21,680
 Waiting feels awkward.

61
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:28,780
 It feels awkward in the world in which we live today, a fast-paced, consumeristic, "I

62
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:30,680
 want it now" kind of world.

63
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:35,800
 In fact, we've put a high value on the things that come immediately.

64
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:41,000
 Like if we have to wait for something, we lower its value.

65
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,360
 The things that are worth it are the things that come quickly.

66
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:48,280
 When I make my Taobao order, it better come in a couple of days.

67
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:50,040
 I don't want to wait weeks.

68
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:54,060
 When I order my food or my coffee, I need it to come quickly.

69
00:03:54,060 --> 00:03:58,160
 When something comes to me quickly, I place a high value on it.

70
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,500
 I see it as a good thing.

71
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:07,100
 We've almost come to see waiting as failure, waiting as if there is a problem.

72
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:12,580
 The scariest symbol that is around all of our lives today is this very symbol.

73
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:14,980
 Nobody likes this symbol.

74
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:18,620
 When this symbol happens, you start freaking out, do you not?

75
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:23,860
 This communicates that something is broken, that something's gone wrong, that you're going

76
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:29,460
 to have to wait for the mobile phone page to load, and nobody wants to wait for the

77
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,100
 page to load.

78
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:34,660
 We do everything as we can as human beings in this day and age to make sure that we don't

79
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:36,320
 wait for anything.

80
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:40,260
 We upgrade our internet at home, but then a month later we complain that YouTube loads

81
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:42,140
 too slowly.

82
00:04:42,140 --> 00:04:47,660
 We are constantly at work trying to make things happen as quickly as possible.

83
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:53,660
 That old story, that old phrase, "Good things come to those who wait," has been replaced

84
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:58,980
 in our generation by "Good things come to those who are first in line, those who act

85
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:03,860
 first, those who act quickest, those that get ahead of the rest.

86
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:06,060
 They're the ones that receive the good things.

87
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:11,100
 Those that wait, well, they get the worst."

88
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:18,020
 It's funny because this idea of kind of being anti-into-waiting has seeped into our Christian

89
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:19,300
 faith.

90
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:24,940
 It's seeped into our churches, into our faith personally, even into our doctrine.

91
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:31,460
 As Christians, we've come to think that God must act, and He must act immediately.

92
00:05:31,460 --> 00:05:37,180
 And if God doesn't act immediately, there's something wrong with God.

93
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:42,460
 It's almost like there's something wrong with Him, and we begin to judge His character,

94
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:48,100
 judge His ability, judge His love for us, even at times judge His existence.

95
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:55,780
 When God doesn't act in the time frame we want Him to act in, we demand an upgrade.

96
00:05:55,780 --> 00:06:02,420
 We really struggle as Christians with this idea that we may have to wait for something.

97
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:05,760
 And if we don't blame God for it, here's what often happens.

98
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:08,020
 We end up blaming ourselves.

99
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:14,380
 Waiting has almost become for Christians a sign of a lack of faith, not faith, a lack

100
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,380
 of faith.

101
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:17,940
 Haven't you been praying about it?

102
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,180
 Haven't you been seeking the Lord?

103
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:20,940
 Well, maybe you haven't fasted yet.

104
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:23,580
 If you fasted, you would receive it.

105
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:28,300
 If you just prayed a bit more, if you got rid of your sin, if you actually confess some

106
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,780
 of those things that you're holding.

107
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:33,060
 Like if you've been waiting ages for your healing, haven't you?

108
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:36,900
 You've been waiting ages for that thing to happen in your life, for that promise to come

109
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:37,900
 through.

110
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:38,900
 Well, God's a good God.

111
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,960
 God wants to give good things to His people.

112
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:45,740
 So if you're waiting, well, there must be something wrong with you.

113
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:52,580
 Either we, as Christians, blame God when things go slow in our spiritual lives, or we blame

114
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,020
 ourselves.

115
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:57,100
 I've experienced both in the waiting seasons of my life.

116
00:06:57,100 --> 00:07:00,380
 I've shared with you many times about the infertility journey that my wife and I went

117
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:05,580
 through and the almost eight years of waiting that it took to go from diagnosis of being

118
00:07:05,580 --> 00:07:08,820
 infertile to receiving our beautiful daughter, Mia.

119
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:10,420
 It was about an eight-year period.

120
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:14,660
 And during that eight-year period, I did not wait well.

121
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:16,020
 I blamed God.

122
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:18,700
 I judged His character.

123
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,860
 I thought that He was distant.

124
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:24,140
 I thought that He was not powerful enough.

125
00:07:24,140 --> 00:07:27,580
 And then after I got over myself for getting over God, I then got on myself that I'm not

126
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,900
 doing the right things.

127
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:33,940
 That obviously if God loved me more or if I pleased Him more, He might act quicker in

128
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:34,940
 my life.

129
00:07:34,940 --> 00:07:39,460
 And so I tried all these things to please God and make Him love me more.

130
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:43,740
 Because if He loved me more, surely He would give me the things that He wants to give me

131
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:50,740
 waiting for us Christians is a really awkward thing.

132
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:53,780
 As we were praying about the beginning of this year, it's funny.

133
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:57,180
 Normally when we start the new year here at the Vine, and I've been involved here in the

134
00:07:57,180 --> 00:08:03,100
 church for almost 30 years now, almost every new year series that we do is a "Woo-hoo,

135
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,620
 pumped up, let's go" series.

136
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:07,500
 It's a one to inspire you, to give you great hope for the year ahead.

137
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:11,780
 But as we were praying for 2026 as a leadership, we felt the Lord say that there are a lot

138
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:20,100
 of people in our community who are waiting and are finding waiting really hard.

139
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:24,500
 I mean, think for a moment about what it is that you might be waiting for in your life.

140
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:29,620
 No doubt that there are seasons of waiting for almost all of us here in different objects,

141
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:34,140
 in different areas with different things.

142
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:38,540
 I think of our asylum seekers and our refugees, some of them who have been waiting for over

143
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:43,660
 10 years for the UNHCR to give them a judgment on their case or the Hong Kong government

144
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:46,740
 to answer something that they've asked for.

145
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:50,940
 Almost over 10 years some of our asylum seekers have been waiting.

146
00:08:50,940 --> 00:08:55,220
 I think of our domestic helpers here who often have to wait a long time before they can go

147
00:08:55,220 --> 00:08:59,860
 back home to their country to visit with their family.

148
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:04,820
 I think of those in our community that have received a promise from God and are waiting

149
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:06,180
 for that promise to come through.

150
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:10,580
 I think of those who are waiting for healing and restoration.

151
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:16,260
 Those who are waiting for that response to a job application or waiting for a new job

152
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,900
 maybe have been waiting for a long time.

153
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:25,380
 I think about those who have been waiting for a spouse, waiting for a new relationship,

154
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:29,380
 waiting for somebody to come through for them, waiting for that phone call to get returned,

155
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:31,940
 waiting for that person to say sorry.

156
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:36,060
 Whatever it might be, all of us know what these seasons of waiting are like and they

157
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:42,400
 are difficult for us because we either have a faulty theology, God is going to act immediately

158
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:48,140
 all the time if he loves, or we have a faulty way of thinking about ourselves, that I'm

159
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:52,220
 broken, that God's punishing me, that this is the reason why I'm in waiting.

160
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:57,780
 So often waiting seasons are hard and we felt as a leadership that there are many of us

161
00:09:57,780 --> 00:10:05,220
 who are struggling, whose hearts are bruised, whose spirits are downcast because of the

162
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:08,620
 wait that we're in.

163
00:10:08,620 --> 00:10:13,420
 Psychologists would tell us that when we wait, we often go through four emotional cycles.

164
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:14,420
 This is interesting.

165
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:15,420
 The first cycle is confusion.

166
00:10:15,420 --> 00:10:17,980
 Why am I waiting?

167
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:19,740
 Like why is this happening?

168
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:20,940
 Why is it happening to me?

169
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:22,860
 I didn't think this was going to happen to me.

170
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:27,020
 So there's a season, a period of confusion.

171
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:30,460
 Often times if the confusion is not dealt with or if the answers don't come, it then

172
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:32,940
 brings us into a place of anxiety.

173
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:35,100
 Am I always going to be like this?

174
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,780
 Is this wait going to be forever?

175
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:38,060
 Will the answer ever come?

176
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:39,300
 Will that phone call ever come?

177
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:41,020
 Will the diagnosis ever come through?

178
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:45,780
 Whatever it might be that we're waiting for, there's this anxiousness within us.

179
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:51,980
 And unless we deal with that anxiety in positive ways, if we try to bury that anxiety, we then

180
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:56,300
 move into the third emotional state, which is a hopelessness.

181
00:10:56,300 --> 00:11:00,660
 And the hopelessness is just like, "Well, I've been waiting for too long."

182
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,420
 The hopelessness is like this kind of attitude.

183
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:09,180
 It's just like a, "It's hard, eh?"

184
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:13,100
 You know, you just kind of like sit down and you're just like, "Well, I guess this is my

185
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,100
 lot in life.

186
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:15,820
 I guess I'm just going to have to wait.

187
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,340
 I guess I'm just going to have to like, whatever.

188
00:11:17,340 --> 00:11:21,420
 I guess, you know, I guess this is just the way it's going to be.

189
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:23,940
 What is, is, is."

190
00:11:23,940 --> 00:11:27,580
 Which then moves us into the fourth state, which is a self-pity state.

191
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,820
 "This is my life.

192
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:30,820
 This is always me.

193
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:32,460
 This always happens to me."

194
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:35,940
 We come in a place where we victimize ourselves.

195
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:39,380
 We feel like the victim of this crazy thing that's happened.

196
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:44,340
 So we go through confusion to anxiety, to hopelessness, to a sense of self-pity.

197
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:46,740
 Perhaps this resonates with some of you.

198
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:50,220
 Maybe you can think about your season of waiting right now and you can say, "Yeah, I'm kind

199
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:51,220
 of in one of these."

200
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:53,900
 And these are linear, but then they're secular as well.

201
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:57,700
 You kind of get to self-pity and then you get confused again, which leads to more anxiety,

202
00:11:57,700 --> 00:12:01,300
 which leads to greater hopelessness, which means more self-pity.

203
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:05,860
 And we're wondering, can the cycle be broken?

204
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:09,180
 What do we do when we need to wait?

205
00:12:09,180 --> 00:12:13,100
 When God is not yet ready to give us the answer?

206
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:19,420
 When he's in control, the dominoes are set, but it's not yet ready for the first one to

207
00:12:19,420 --> 00:12:20,420
 get pushed.

208
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:29,140
 How do we as Christians find hope, healing, restoration for our souls and our hearts,

209
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:34,180
 even when the promise is still a long way off?

210
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:37,500
 This is what we felt as a leadership for God for us to speak into in the start of this

211
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,780
 year.

212
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:43,940
 You'll be encouraged to know that there are over 200 passages in Scripture that speak

213
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,640
 on the topic of waiting.

214
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,100
 So waiting is not a new thing in Scripture at all.

215
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:51,820
 Waiting is deeply embedded in the stories of God.

216
00:12:51,820 --> 00:12:56,140
 You look at some of the greatest people of faith, and they had to often wait long periods

217
00:12:56,140 --> 00:13:00,640
 of time before they received the thing that they had on their heart from the Lord.

218
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:04,740
 So there's over 200 passages in the Bible about waiting.

219
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:10,260
 As preparation for this series, I did a little overview of those 200 passages, and I noticed

220
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:14,860
 something that I wouldn't have thought going into this, and this is the reality, that the

221
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:21,900
 Bible predominantly speaks about seasons of waiting as a gift.

222
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:25,340
 That sounds a bit funny because they haven't been much of a gift for me in my life.

223
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:27,460
 I don't know about you in your life.

224
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:33,100
 Now that doesn't mean that the Bible downplays the emotions that come alongside of a waiting

225
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,100
 period.

226
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:38,220
 There's a lot of stuff in Scripture that helps us when we're feeling anxious and confused

227
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,540
 and we're feeling hopeless.

228
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:44,300
 There's a lot of things within God's Word that can meet us in those emotional moments

229
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:49,020
 of waiting, but the predominant discussion about waiting in Scripture is that waiting

230
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:56,500
 is a season of a gift, that it's a way for you to slow down, to take the foot off the

231
00:13:56,500 --> 00:14:01,580
 gas a little bit, to receive something that perhaps you wouldn't have received if you'd

